                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/281: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-30T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received August 30, 4.36 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese Government inquires of the Diplomatic Corps whether the embargo on arms
                    and ammunition includes raw material for the manufacture of the same. I have the
                    honor to request your instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
